%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22Information%20Blackout%20on%20Cheetahs'%20Health%20and%20Status%20Hurts%20Them%2C%20Some%20Experts%20Say%20Not%20in%20Loop%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F17142504%2FScreenshot-2023-09-17-at-2.24.53-PM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EBengaluru%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Two%20cheetah%20experts%20who%20were%20actively%20involved%20in%20the%20introduction%20of%20African%20cheetahs%20in%20India%20%E2%80%93%20as%20part%20of%20Project%20Cheetah%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20ambitious%20intercontinental%20cheetah%20translocation%20programme%20%E2%80%93%20are%20no%20longer%20in%20the%20loop%20about%20the%20animals%E2%80%99%20management%20or%20their%20health%20status%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20has%20learnt.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESo%20far%2C%2010%20cheetahs%20%E2%80%93%20seven%20adults%20and%20three%20cubs%20%E2%80%93%20have%20died%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%E2%80%99s%20Kuno%20National%20Park%2C%20where%20Project%20Cheetah%20is%20ongoing.%20The%20tenth%20death%20%E2%80%93%20of%20Shaurya%2C%20a%20male%20from%20Namibia%20%E2%80%93%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fanother-african-cheetah-dies-10-deaths-so-far-at-kuno-national-park%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eoccurred%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20January%2016.%20While%20post-mortem%20results%20that%20will%20give%20us%20insight%20into%20the%20reason%20behind%20the%20cheetah%E2%80%99s%20death%20in%20its%20enclosure%20are%20still%20awaited%2C%20monitoring%20teams%20on%20the%20ground%20observed%20that%20the%20animal%20showed%20a%20staggering%20gait%20and%20weakness%20before%20it%20died.%20Shaurya%20is%20one%20of%20the%20eight%20cheetahs%20that%20arrived%20from%20Namibia%20in%202022%2C%20and%20with%20which%20Project%20Cheetah%20kicked%20off%20%E2%80%93%20launched%20in%20person%20by%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20on%20his%20birthday%20on%20September%2017%20that%20year.%20Twelve%20more%20adult%20cheetahs%20arrived%20from%20South%20Africa%20in%20February%202023%2C%20bringing%20the%20total%20number%20of%20adult%20cheetahs%20to%2020.%20Thirteen%20of%20the%20adult%20cheetahs%20now%20remain%20in%20Kuno.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELaurie%20Marker%2C%20a%20Namibia-based%20cheetah%20expert%2C%20and%20Adrian%20Tordiffe%2C%20a%20South%20African%20cheetah%20expert%20currently%20based%20in%20India%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20they%20are%20not%20getting%20information%20about%20the%20animals%20except%20for%20media%20reports.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20has%20reached%20out%20to%20the%20National%20Tiger%20Conservation%20Authority%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%20implementing%20Project%20Cheetah%20%E2%80%93%20to%20ascertain%20if%20any%20of%20the%20other%20two%20experts%20are%20being%20kept%20in%20the%20loop%20regarding%20cheetah%20releases%20and%20their%20health%20conditions.%20It%20is%20best%20to%20keep%20at%20least%20one%20expert%20in%20the%20loop%20since%20they%20have%20direct%20experience%20working%20with%20African%20cheetahs%2C%20an%20Indian%20veterinary%20officer%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ENo%20information%20except%20for%20media%20reports%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELaurie%20Marker%2C%20founder%20and%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20Cheetah%20Conservation%20Fund%2C%20was%20involved%20with%20the%20release%20of%20the%20first%20batch%20of%20cheetahs%20that%20came%20in%20from%20Namibia%20on%20September%2017%20in%202022.%20According%20to%20the%20news%20agency%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Findias-reintroduction-project-on-course-despite-challenges-says-cheetah-conservation-fund%2Farticleshow%2F103728213.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EPTI%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20Marker%20has%20been%20%E2%80%9Cinstrumental%20in%20drafting%20plans%E2%80%9D%20for%20India%E2%80%99s%20cheetah%20introduction%20and%20has%20traveled%20to%20India%20several%20times%20since%202009%20for%20this.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20not%20getting%20information%20except%20for%20media%20reports%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Marker%2C%20in%20an%20email%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20asked%20whether%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EMarker%20or%20the%20Cheetah%20Conservation%20Fund%20are%20still%20involved%20with%20Project%20Cheetah%20in%20any%20capacity%2C%20and%20whether%20Marker%20was%20consulted%20when%20some%20of%20the%20cheetahs%20were%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2F4th-cheetah-released-wild-kuno-national-park-tourists-glimpse-9078047%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereleased%20into%20the%20wild%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20this%20year%20despite%20months%20of%20captivity%20after%20they%20were%20restricted%20to%20enclosures%20for%20health%20check%20ups%20following%20a%20series%20of%20deaths%20last%20year%2C%20Marker%20gave%20no%20direct%20answer%3B%20instead%2C%20she%20said%20that%20it%20was%20an%20%E2%80%9CIndia%20project%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20spent%20nearly%20a%20year%20on%20the%20ground%20teaching%20about%20cheetah%20and%20the%20reintroduction.%20We%20hope%20that%20our%20work%20with%20them%20in%20training%20will%20pay%20off%20for%20the%20cheetahs%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20wrote%20in%20an%20email%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F27223624%2FUntitled-design-74.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F27223624%2FUntitled-design-74.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F27223624%2FUntitled-design-74-300x140.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F27223624%2FUntitled-design-74-1024x478.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-645937%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESasha%2C%20a%20female%20cheetah%2C%20at%20Kuno%20National%20Park.%20Photo%3A%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20State%20Forest%20Department.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAdrian%20Tordiffe%2C%20a%20veterinary%20wildlife%20specialist%20currently%20based%20in%20India%2C%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20the%20last%20direct%20communication%20that%20he%20obtained%20from%20Indian%20authorities%20about%20the%20animals%20was%20on%20July%2018%2C%20and%20that%20he%20has%20not%20received%20any%20information%20since%20then.%20In%20an%20exclusive%20interview%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20he%20added%20that%20he%20was%20gradually%20%E2%80%9Costracised%E2%80%9D%20from%20the%20Project%2C%20possibly%20because%20he%20spoke%20to%20the%20media%20about%20the%20cheetah%20deaths%20that%20had%20occurred%20during%20that%20time.%20He%20did%20not%20receive%20any%20information%20about%20the%20death%20of%20the%20seventh%20adult%20cheetah%20on%20January%2016%20either%2C%20he%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20post-mortem%20results%20are%20still%20awaited%20%E2%80%93%20more%20than%20four%20days%20after%20the%20cheetah%E2%80%99s%20death.%20Last%20year%2C%20Tordiffe%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20the%20wait%20for%20the%20post-mortem%20results%20and%20not%20sharing%20information%20with%20the%20African%20experts%20had%20caused%20a%20delay%20in%20identifying%20the%20cause%20of%20the%20first%20cheetah%20death%20due%20to%20septicaemia%20(officially%20listed%20as%20a%20natural%20death%20due%20to%20%E2%80%9Ctraumatic%20shock%E2%80%9D%20by%20Indian%20authorities).%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFollowing%20this%2C%20two%20more%20cheetahs%20died%20in%20a%20similar%20manner%20and%20these%20deaths%20could%20have%20been%20possibly%20avoided%20had%20the%20experts%20been%20in%20the%20loop%2C%20he%20had%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20has%20been%20no%20formal%20communication%20with%20me%20regarding%20my%20involvement%20in%20the%20project%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20the%20exclusive%20interview%20dated%20January%2021.%20%E2%80%9CI%20have%20written%20to%20the%20chair%20of%20the%20Project%20Cheetah%20Steering%20Committee%20hoping%20for%20some%20reconciliation.%20He%20did%20not%20even%20acknowledge%20receipt%20of%20my%20letter.%20It%20seemed%20a%20waste%20of%20time%20to%20pursue%20the%20matter%20further.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20main%20problem%20with%20Project%20Cheetah%20is%20the%20%E2%80%9Csecrecy%2C%20political%20rivalry%20and%20the%20egos%20of%20the%20people%20involved%E2%80%9D%2C%20Tordiffe%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fproject-cheetah-deaths-radio-collar-infections%5C%22%3EProject%20Cheetah%3A%20Radio%20Collar%20Infections%20a%20%E2%80%98Cause%20for%20Concern%E2%80%99%2C%20Team%20Expert%20Questions%20Ground%20Support%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EPolitics%20over%20science%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20high%20profile%20nature%20of%20the%20project%20has%20created%20a%20situation%20where%20certain%20people%20stand%20to%20gain%20significant%20political%20points%20with%20those%20in%20power%E2%80%A6This%20was%20always%20going%20to%20be%20a%20challenging%20project%20as%20we%20had%20no%20real%20template%20or%20precedent%20to%20work%20from.%20It%20was%20critical%20that%20accurate%20scientific%20data%20was%20collected%20and%20shared%20in%20an%20open%20and%20transparent%20manner%20with%20all%20involved.%20Unfortunately%20that%20did%20not%20happen.%20The%20flow%20of%20information%20is%20now%20tightly%20controlled%20and%20it%20is%20difficult%20to%20know%20what%20to%20believe%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20Tordiffe%2C%20the%20biggest%20challenge%20%E2%80%9Cis%20that%20management%20decisions%20there%20seem%20to%20be%20based%20on%20politics%20rather%20than%20science%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CScience%20cannot%20advance%20in%20a%20society%20where%20information%20is%20controlled%20by%20those%20in%20power%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20scientists%20are%20silenced%2C%20conspiracy%20theories%20are%20allowed%20to%20thrive%20and%20people%20and%20animals%20end%20up%20suffering%20unnecessarily.%20The%20truth%20is%20the%20truth%2C%20even%20if%20it%20is%20difficult%20to%20face%2C%20authorities%20just%20do%20not%20want%20to%20acknowledge%20that%20they%20do%20not%20have%20all%20the%20answers.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBoth%20Tordiffe%20(along%20with%20other%20cheetah%20and%20veterinary%20experts%20Vincent%20van%20der%20Merwe%2C%20Andrew%20Fraser%20and%20Mike%20Toft)%20and%20Marker%20had%20written%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20July%20last%20year%20in%20two%20separate%20letters%20regarding%20similar%20issues%3A%20about%20their%20concerns%20in%20being%20kept%20in%20the%20dark%20about%20the%20management%20of%20Project%20Cheetah%20and%20the%20animals%E2%80%99%20health.%20In%20their%20letters%2C%20they%20noted%20that%20some%20of%20the%20cheetah%20deaths%20%E2%80%9Ccould%20have%20been%20prevented%20by%20better%20monitoring%20of%20the%20animals%20and%20more%20appropriate%E2%80%9D%20and%20timely%20%E2%80%9Cveterinary%20care%E2%80%9D%20if%20the%20experts%20were%20informed%20immediately%20rather%20than%20being%20%E2%80%9Cignored%E2%80%9D%20and%20used%20as%20mere%20%E2%80%9Cwindow-dressing%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fhave-serious-concerns-how-cheetah-project-is-managed-we-in-dark-foreign-experts-tell-sc-8872128%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereported%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Later%2C%20however%2C%20both%20van%20der%20Merwe%20and%20Fraser%20dissociated%20themselves%20from%20the%20letter.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20has%20written%20to%20the%20National%20Tiger%20Conservation%20Authority%20(NTCA)%20for%20details%20about%20whether%20experts%20Tordiffe%20and%20Marker%2C%20or%20the%20two%20others%20listed%20on%20the%20same%20panel%20%E2%80%93%20Fraser%20and%20van%20der%20Merwe%20%E2%80%93%20are%20being%20informed%20about%20the%20cheetahs%E2%80%99%20health%20and%20status%2C%20or%20being%20solicited%20for%20information%20regarding%20the%20animals%E2%80%99%20health%20and%20release%20into%20the%20wild%20after%20several%20months%20of%20captivity.%20The%20story%20will%20be%20updated%20when%20they%20respond.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscience.thewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fkuno-project-cheetah-carrying-capacity%2F%5C%22%3EDid%20India%20Get%20Its%20Math%20Wrong%20About%20How%20Many%20Cheetahs%20Can%20Fit%20In%20Kuno%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E