%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fboris-johnson-claims-the-world-would-be-more-stable-under-donald-trump-13052064%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Germany%20Celebrates%20250%20Years%20of%20Caspar%20David%20Friedrich%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F20120618%2Fimage-1769.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSave%20the%20Year%2C%E2%80%9D%20notes%20the%20website%20dedicated%20to%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcaspardavid250.de%2Fen%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22External%20link%20%E2%80%94%20Caspar%20David%20Friedrich's%20250th%20anniversary%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECaspar%20David%20Friedrich%E2%80%99s%20250th%20anniversary%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20Germany%20will%20celebrate%20throughout%202024%20with%20a%20variety%20of%20events%20and%20exhibitions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Hamburger%20Kunsthalle%20opens%20its%20exhibition%20dedicated%20to%20the%20Romantic%20painter%20on%20December%2015%2C%20the%20anniversary%20year%20officially%20starts%20on%20on%20January%2020%C2%A0at%20St.%20Nicholas%E2%80%99%20Cathedral%20in%20Greifswald%2C%20where%20Friedrich%20was%20baptized.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20legacy%20of%20the%20painter%20was%20already%20making%20headlines%20ahead%20of%20the%20official%20celebrations%2C%20when%20one%20of%20his%20sketchbooks%20sold%20for%20%E2%82%AC1.8%20million%20(nearly%20%242%20million)%20at%C2%A0auction%20in%20Berlin%20at%20the%20end%20of%20November.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShortly%20before%20the%20sale%2C%20Berlin%E2%80%99s%20Senate%20Department%20for%20Culture%C2%A0initiated%20proceedings%20to%20have%20Friedrich%E2%80%99s%20work%20entered%20in%20the%20Berlin%20state%20register%20of%20nationally%20valuable%20cultural%20assets.%20This%20stopped%20buyers%C2%A0outside%C2%A0of%20Germany%20taking%20the%20sketchbook%20out%C2%A0of%20the%20country%20%E2%80%94%20at%20least%20until%20after%20the%20conclusion%20of%20those%20proceedings.%20Even%20then%2C%20it%20would%20only%20be%20possible%20to%20export%20the%20sketchbook%20if%20it%20fails%20to%20meet%20criteria%20deeming%20it%20a%20valuable%20cultural%20asset.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20look%20at%20the%20item%E2%80%99s%20provenance%2C%20however%2C%20shows%20that%20it%20is%20indeed%20a%20truly%20unique%20treasure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENationally%20valuable%20cultural%20asset%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%E2%80%9CKarlsruhe%20Sketchbook%2C%E2%80%9D%20as%20it%20is%20known%2C%20had%20been%20in%20the%20possession%20of%20the%20Kersting%20family%20for%20over%20200%20years.%20Georg%20Friedrich%20Kersting%2C%20a%20notable%20German%20Romantic%20painter%20in%20his%20own%20right%2C%20was%20a%20close%20friend%20of%20Caspar%20David%20Friedrich%20%E2%80%93%20who%20was%20born%20in%20Greifswald%2C%20now%20in%20the%20state%20of%20Mecklenburg-Western%20Pomerania%2C%20on%20September%205%2C%201774.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20recently%20published%20book%20on%20Caspar%20David%20Friedrich%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.in%2FZauber-Stille-Caspar-Friedrichs-Zeiten-ebook%2Fdp%2FB0C263HXFK%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EZauber%20der%20Stille%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20(Magic%20of%20Silence)%2C%20German%20author%20Florian%20Illies%20writes%20that%20the%20artist%E2%80%99s%20contemporaries%20reported%20Kersting%20helping%20his%20friend%20with%20the%20depictions%20of%20figures%20in%20his%20paintings.%20Why%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIllies%20writes%20that%C2%A0Friedrich%20was%20considered%20a%20less-than-talented%20portraitist%2C%20for%20which%20he%20was%20even%20ridiculed%20during%20his%20time%20at%20the%20art%20academy%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fcopenhagen%2Ft-38984232%5C%22%3ECopenhagen%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIs%20that%20the%20reason%20the%20figures%20in%20Friedrich%E2%80%99s%20paintings%20are%20usually%20seen%20from%20behind%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStrokes%20of%20fate%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECaspar%20David%20Friedrich%20was%20the%20sixth%20child%20of%20Greifswald%20soap%20boiler%20and%20chandler%20Adolf%20Gottlieb%20Friedrich%20and%20his%20wife%2C%20Sophie%20Dorothea.%20She%20died%20in%201781%2C%20and%20one%20of%20his%20sisters%20died%20a%20year%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEspecially%20traumatic%20was%20the%201787%20death%20of%20his%20younger%20brother%20Johann%20Christopher.%20There%20are%20conflicting%20stories%20of%20what%20happened%2C%20with%20some%20accounts%20saying%20the%20younger%20boy%20drowned%20while%20trying%20to%20save%20Caspar%20David%2C%20who%20had%20broken%20through%20ice%20while%20skating.%20Of%20the%20painter%E2%80%99s%20nine%20siblings%2C%20only%20five%20survived%20to%20adulthood.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201790%2C%20Friedrich%20began%20his%20studies%20under%C2%A0Greifswald%20University%20architecture%20and%20drawing%20teacher%20Johann%20Gottfried%20Quistorp%2C%20who%20gave%20him%20particular%20encouragement.%20Friedrich%20continued%20his%20artistic%20studies%20at%20the%20art%20academy%20in%20Copenhagen.%20From%201798%2C%20Friedrich%20lived%20and%20worked%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fdresden%2Ft-19110721%5C%22%3EDresden%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20he%20died%20on%20May%207%2C%201840.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAdmired%20by%20many%20%E2%80%93%20but%20not%20Goethe%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMystic%20with%20a%20paintbrush%E2%80%9D%20is%20how%20Swedish%20poet%20Per%20Daniel%20Amadeus%20Atterbom%20described%20Caspar%20David%20Friedrich.%20The%20Romantic%20painter%20gained%20the%20admiration%20of%20his%20colleagues%20during%20his%20lifetime.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20one%20notable%20exception%2C%20however%3A%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fjohann-wolfgang-von-goethe%2Ft-63006215%5C%22%3EJohann%20Wolfgang%20von%20Goethe%3C%2Fa%3E%20did%20not%20know%20what%20to%20make%20of%20Friedrich%E2%80%99s%20paintings.%20He%20derided%20them%20as%20%E2%80%9CNew%20German%2C%20religiously%20patriotic.%E2%80%9D%20The%20poet%20is%20even%20said%20to%20have%20smashed%20one%20of%20the%20artist%E2%80%99s%20paintings%20on%20the%20edge%20of%20a%20table%20because%20he%20didn%E2%80%99t%20like%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201794%2C%20Friedrich%20attended%20the%20art%20academy%20in%20Copenhagen%2C%20where%20he%20first%20encountered%20the%20nature%20mysticism%20that%20would%20so%20strongly%C2%A0influence%20his%20artwork.%20His%20first%20oil%20painting%20was%20provocative%3A%20the%20work%20%E2%80%9CCross%20in%20the%20Mountains%E2%80%9D%20from%201807%2F1808%20deals%20with%20the%20relationship%20of%20nature%20and%20God.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20then%20on%2C%20Friedrich%E2%80%99s%20work%20was%20no%20longer%20the%20Enlightenment%E2%80%99s%20window%20on%20the%20world%2C%20but%20a%20window%20to%20the%20soul%2C%20in%20the%20spirit%20of%20Romanticism.%20%E2%80%9CCross%20in%20the%20Mountains%E2%80%9D%20caused%20a%20stir%20because%20in%20it%2C%20the%20painter%20gave%20equal%20space%20to%20both%20the%20church%20and%20nature.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F20115120%2Fimage-1764.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22868%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F20115120%2Fimage-1764.png%20868w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F20115120%2Fimage-1764-287x300.png%20287w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-693735%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22907%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ECross%20in%20the%20Mountains%20(Tetschen%20Altar)%20(1808)%20Friedrich%E2%80%99s%20first%20major%20work%2C%20the%20piece%20breaks%20with%20the%20traditional%20representation%20of%20crucifixion%20in%20altarpieces%20by%20depicting%20the%20scene%20as%20a%20landscape.%20Photo%3A%20Public%20Domain%2FWikimedia%20Commons%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20patriot%20and%20eccentric%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFriedrich%20was%20a%20reclusive%20eccentric%20who%20only%20left%20his%20house%20in%20Dresden%20for%20long%20walks%20after%20dusk.%20On%20January%2021%2C%201818%2C%20he%20married%2025-year-old%20Caroline%20Bommer%20%E2%80%93%20at%206%20o%E2%80%99clock%20in%20the%20morning.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20unsettled%20by%20the%C2%A0military%20campaigns%20of%C2%A0%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fridley-scotts-napoleon-makes-waves%2Fa-67486394%5C%22%3ENapoleon%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20the%20presence%20of%20French%20troops%20because%20they%20threatened%20him%20and%20his%20homeland.%20By%201806%2C%20Napoleon%20had%20occupied%20the%20majority%20of%20German%20territory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20sparked%20nationalist%C2%A0sentiments%20in%20Friedrich.%20The%20artist%20dreamed%20of%20the%20ideal%20of%20a%20united%20Germany%20and%20had%20equal%20reverence%20for%20both%20the%20Christian%20and%20the%20Germanic.%20His%20paintings%20often%20feature%20figures%20wearing%20traditional%20German%20costumes%2C%20a%20subtle%20expression%20of%20patriotism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EInvented%20landscapes%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%C2%A0Friedrich%E2%80%99s%20brush%20and%20pencil%20faithfully%20captured%20each%20tree%2C%20cliff%2C%20mountain%20or%20unfurled%20sail%2C%20in%20his%20works%20he%20freely%20reassembled%20those%20individually%20observed%20elements.%20Nature%20was%C2%A0an%20inspiration%20for%20him%2C%20not%20a%20template.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20combined%20his%20impressions%20into%20invented%20landscapes%20from%20his%20own%20imagination%2C%20such%20as%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Sea%20of%20Ice.%E2%80%9D%20The%20apocalyptic%20painting%20turns%20the%20frozen%20Elbe%20River%20into%20a%20wide%20sea%2C%20with%20a%20shipwreck%20crushed%20between%20slabs%20of%20thick%20ice%2C%20ominously%20piled%20high%20in%20the%20center%20of%20the%20image%20%E2%80%93%20a%20scene%20never%20witnessed%20by%20Friedrich%2C%20only%20imagined%20by%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUntil%20his%20death%20in%201820%2C%20he%20lived%20just%20a%20stone%E2%80%99s%20throw%20from%20the%20Elbe%20River.%20His%20house%2C%20at%20An%20der%20Elbe%2033%20in%20Dresden%2C%20was%20where%20he%20hosted%20future%20Russian%20Czar%20Nicholas%20I%2C%20who%20bought%20several%20of%20his%20paintings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEnlightenment%20rationale%20gives%20way%20to%20emotion%20of%20romanticism%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Enlightenment%20emphasized%20reason%20and%20a%20rational%20understanding%20of%20the%20world%2C%20the%20Romantic%20period%20that%20followed%20was%20marked%20by%20emotion%20and%20sensitivity.%20Subjective%20moods%20were%20given%20prominence%2C%20which%20can%20be%20seen%20in%20the%20art%20of%20Caspar%20David%20Friedrich.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFriedrich%20responded%20to%20the%20strict%20compositions%20of%20the%20Enlightenment%20with%20disquiet%20and%20emotion%3A%20jagged%20mountain%20landscapes%2C%20morning%20mist%2C%20gloomy%20layers%20of%20cloud%20that%20sometimes%20threaten%20to%20swallow%20people%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20his%20major%20works%20is%20%E2%80%9CMonk%20by%20the%20Sea%2C%E2%80%9D%20which%20he%20began%20in%201808.%20It%E2%80%99s%20considered%20one%20of%20his%20most%20unconventional%20works%2C%20as%20there%20is%20no%20sense%20of%20spatial%20perspective%3B%20sea%20and%20sky%20merge.%20In%20the%20foreground%2C%20a%20small%20and%20reverent%20man%20stands%20with%20his%20back%20turned%20to%20the%20viewer%20%E2%80%93%20thus%20acting%20as%20a%20proxy%20and%20a%20figure%20of%20identification.%20Infinity%20and%20the%20enormity%20of%20the%20universe%20are%20the%20themes%20of%20the%20painting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%2