24%2F01%2Fsustainable-nature-retreat-5-1705577667-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2Fsustainable-nature-retreat-5-1705577667-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2Fsustainable-nature-retreat-5-1705577667-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2Fsustainable-nature-retreat-5-1705577667-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-338525%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20canvas%20tents%20ensure%20sunlight%20floods%20the%20rooms%20and%20opens%20out%20onto%20a%20porch%20where%20one%20can%20view%20the%20wilderness%2C%20Picture%20source%3A%20Luv%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnce%20famous%20as%20the%20epitome%20of%20tiger%20tourism%20in%20Rajasthan%2C%20the%20800%20sq%20m%20area%20of%20the%20Sariska%20Tiger%20Reserve%20was%20the%20perfect%20home%20to%20the%20beasts%20owing%20to%20its%20mountains%2C%20grasslands%20and%20cliffs.%20A%202002%20survey%20by%20the%20National%20Tiger%20Conservation%20Authority%20(NTCA)%20revealed%2016%20tigers%20present%20in%20the%20area.%20Three%20years%20later%2C%20there%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20a%20single%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPoaching%20was%20suspected%20to%20be%20the%20primary%20cause.%20A%20joint%20investigation%20by%20the%20Rajasthan%20police%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F334337%2Fbest-homestays-for-wildlife-safari-in-india-national-park-kanha-bandhavgarh-mudumalai%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eforest%20department%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20NTCA%20led%20to%20the%20culprits%20%E2%80%94%20a%20local%20poachers%20gang%20that%20had%20been%20using%20traps%2C%20poisoned%20bait%2C%20and%20other%20illegal%20means%20to%20hunt%20the%20tigers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20investigation%2C%20the%20Governme